WEBVTT

00:03.625 --> 00:07.375
[Meredith] <i>People often ask</i>
<i>what I've learned </i><i>from surviving COVID.</i>

00:07.458 --> 00:08.917
[seagulls crying]

00:09.250 --> 00:12.250
<i>I know they mean well,</i>
<i>but it's </i><i>a really annoying question.</i>

00:15.500 --> 00:19.417
<i>Being away from work, </i><i>my children,</i>
<i>getting hooked up to a vent...</i>

00:21.333 --> 00:23.583
<i>it's not exactly a masterclass.</i>

00:26.500 --> 00:28.333
<i>Though it did teach me </i><i>something.</i>

00:30.333 --> 00:32.291
<i>It taught me </i><i>that I'm still alive.</i>

00:33.583 --> 00:37.166
♪

00:37.250 --> 00:38.834
[horns honking, clock ticking]

00:38.917 --> 00:44.667
♪

00:46.250 --> 00:48.792
Did you know that every avocado
sold commercially

00:48.875 --> 00:52.166
originates from a tree
this one dude had in his backyard?

00:52.250 --> 00:57.041
No, but did I know that an avocado
has more potassium than a banana.

00:57.125 --> 00:59.542
Well, did you know that
if you ate 400 bananas,

00:59.625 --> 01:01.166
you might overdose on potassium?

01:01.250 --> 01:03.625
Why would you say that?
You know I worry about dying.

01:03.709 --> 01:05.125
[screams]

01:05.208 --> 01:08.166
Okay, whoa.
We'll shut up. Please don't evict us.

01:08.250 --> 01:09.583
[Taryn] That's not our stuff.

01:09.667 --> 01:11.000
Are you evicting yourself?

01:11.083 --> 01:12.625
I'm smart and I'm capable

01:12.709 --> 01:15.750
and I have made livable homes
out of the humblest of places,

01:15.834 --> 01:16.834
including my car.

01:16.917 --> 01:18.375
But I deserve more than just livable.

01:18.458 --> 01:22.417
And so does Luna,
so I am fighting for her.

01:22.500 --> 01:23.750
I'm rich. Ha!

01:23.834 --> 01:26.417
Technically, I am rich.
I own part of the hospital.

01:26.500 --> 01:30.083
So I'm gonna sell my shares
and hire a lawyer to help me adopt Luna.

01:30.166 --> 01:33.583
And then, I'm taking whatever money's left
and moving to a place

01:33.667 --> 01:36.792
where I don't have to listen
to people argue about fruit!

01:36.875 --> 01:38.000
<i>♪ Yeah, yeah ♪</i>

01:38.083 --> 01:40.583
-Dibs on the bed.
-[sighs]

01:40.667 --> 01:43.750
[laughs] But explaining that
to my ex-husband

01:43.834 --> 01:45.458
was like a full-time job.

01:45.542 --> 01:47.583
[chuckles] Sounds like it.

01:47.667 --> 01:48.917
-You paged?
-Oh, hey.

01:49.000 --> 01:50.583
Dr. Altman, this is, uh, Sophie.

01:50.667 --> 01:52.333
She was in a little fender bender.

01:52.417 --> 01:54.291
She's all clear except her
heart rate is a little high.

01:54.375 --> 01:55.959
So I thought you should check on her EKG.

01:56.041 --> 01:59.000
I told him it's probably just
white coat syndrome.

01:59.083 --> 02:01.625
One look at him
and my heart's off to the races.

02:01.709 --> 02:03.625
-[laughter]
-Oh, sorry.

02:03.709 --> 02:06.458
Keep forgetting it's COVID
and you can't just touch people.

02:06.542 --> 02:08.125
Don't worry, I'm wearing protection.

02:08.208 --> 02:09.709
[laughs]

02:10.709 --> 02:12.125
-[chuckles]
-Okay.

02:12.208 --> 02:13.792
I, uh-- I'll come back and check on you.

02:13.875 --> 02:15.959
-See you soon, Sophie.
-Hope so.

02:16.041 --> 02:19.083
-Oh, you're wearing protection?
-I didn't mean it how it sounds.

02:19.166 --> 02:22.250
-Well, she's throwing herself at you.
-No, she's just nervous.

02:22.333 --> 02:23.917
Well, I can give her
your number, if you want.

02:24.000 --> 02:26.375
-Oh, really?
-No. [laughs]

02:26.458 --> 02:27.875
-[elevator dings]
-Now, look.

02:27.959 --> 02:29.875
As Residency Director,

02:29.959 --> 02:32.458
you're not only teaching them
to do surgery,

02:32.542 --> 02:36.125
but you're-- you're guiding them.
When a resident loses a patient,

02:36.208 --> 02:37.792
it's your shoulder they cry on.

02:37.875 --> 02:41.083
If they succeed, you're their cheerleader.
So, essentially, they--

02:41.166 --> 02:43.417
-You're on call 24 hours a day.
-[laughter]

02:43.500 --> 02:45.083
That's the way you always
described it to me.

02:45.166 --> 02:47.375
I appreciate the advice.
I do know how to do the job.

02:47.458 --> 02:49.208
I've been watching you do it
my whole career.

02:49.291 --> 02:52.000
If I were you, I would be doing
the surgeries that I don't get to do.

02:52.083 --> 02:53.500
[Richard] Well, you're the only one
I wanted for the job.

02:53.583 --> 02:55.291
We'll see you at the wedding.

02:55.375 --> 02:57.875
So, you gonna give Richard's speech
or did you write your own?

02:57.959 --> 02:59.500
-No speech. No--
-No speech?

02:59.583 --> 03:00.959
No.

03:01.041 --> 03:02.417
[Cheers and applause]

03:02.500 --> 03:03.917
[Meredith] No, no, no, no, no.

03:04.000 --> 03:06.500
Okay, we admitted 10 patients
last night with COVID symptoms.

03:06.583 --> 03:09.417
What are the statuses of all 10 patients?

03:11.709 --> 03:15.667
[woman over P.A.] <i>Cardio tech, room 342.</i>
<i>Cardio tech, room 342.</i>

03:16.458 --> 03:17.875
Give the O2 a minute, Gerlie.

03:17.959 --> 03:19.875
We'll increase it if your sats
don't come back up.

03:19.959 --> 03:22.583
Or you could present the patient to me,

03:22.667 --> 03:25.417
and I could decide if we should
increase it right now.

03:25.500 --> 03:26.917
Present, Schmitt.

03:27.000 --> 03:31.250
Gerlie Bernardo, 37,
admitted this morning with sats of--

03:31.333 --> 03:33.166
88. Temp was 102.

03:33.250 --> 03:37.500
Heart rate 105, BP 96/54. Dehydrated.

03:37.583 --> 03:40.166
I'm a nurse, long-term care.

03:40.250 --> 03:43.667
Gotten pretty good at knowing
when to call the ambulance.

03:43.750 --> 03:45.542
Private or at a facility?

03:45.625 --> 03:49.166
Lakeforest... assisted living.

03:49.250 --> 03:51.125
I'm guessing that's where
I picked this up.

03:51.208 --> 03:55.458
But I've helped take care
of Earl for seven years.

03:55.542 --> 03:58.792
Even when he has COVID,
I'm still helping him to the bathroom.

03:58.875 --> 04:00.291
He's 96.

04:00.375 --> 04:02.333
The kindest person I know.

04:02.417 --> 04:04.208
My parents were at Silver Villas.

04:04.750 --> 04:06.208
They were hit hard.

04:06.500 --> 04:07.750
Yes, they were.

04:07.834 --> 04:11.417
So, let's put her on high-flow,
order chest films,

04:11.500 --> 04:13.709
and start steroids and Remdesivir.

04:15.333 --> 04:17.208
[monitor beeping]

04:17.291 --> 04:22.500
♪

04:24.417 --> 04:30.250
♪

04:30.333 --> 04:32.250
How did Luna do?

04:32.333 --> 04:33.625
Couldn't have been better.

04:34.333 --> 04:37.750
Hate that CPS made the poor thing wait
a week before approving her surgery, but--

04:38.333 --> 04:40.583
[woman over P.A.] <i>Nurse Kaiser to the OR.</i>

04:40.667 --> 04:42.542
Your name will be back up there soon.

04:42.625 --> 04:44.250
I don't know. They gave me an office.

04:44.333 --> 04:45.417
-And a desk.
-Mm.

04:45.500 --> 04:48.250
-And a chair.
-Wow, a chair?

04:48.333 --> 04:50.250
-They must really fancy you.
-[chuckles]

04:50.333 --> 04:52.083
You could have just said no, you know.

04:52.166 --> 04:53.750
When I asked you out for a drink.

04:53.834 --> 04:55.917
You didn't have to pass out
and spend two months in the hospital

04:56.000 --> 04:57.166
just to avoid turning me down.

04:57.250 --> 04:59.333
-That seems like a lifetime ago.
-Mm-hmm.

05:00.834 --> 05:02.083
Did I hear you?

05:02.166 --> 05:05.625
Did you come to my room and tell me
to fight and talk about my kids?

05:05.709 --> 05:06.583
Couldn't have been me.

05:06.667 --> 05:09.250
I'm far too busy to do sickbed visits.

05:09.333 --> 05:11.500
Must have been some other Irishman
hanging around around here.

05:11.583 --> 05:12.500
[laughs]

05:12.583 --> 05:15.208
That being said,
I am glad you didn't die, Grey.

05:15.291 --> 05:16.834
Me too.

05:18.834 --> 05:20.083
You'll get back there soon.

05:20.792 --> 05:21.917
I should get going.

05:22.667 --> 05:25.792
-My sister is getting married.
-Mm-hmm.

05:25.875 --> 05:29.792
♪

05:29.875 --> 05:32.917
...as long as we both shall live.

05:35.208 --> 05:37.125
Now, very important question.

05:37.208 --> 05:40.208
Is there anyone here
who objects to this union?

05:40.291 --> 05:41.458
Oh, well, we do!

05:41.542 --> 05:42.667
[laughter]

05:42.750 --> 05:44.083
He-- He was kidding, Nana.

05:44.166 --> 05:46.834
Well, we aren't. I'm sorry, Maggie.

05:46.917 --> 05:48.834
Wait, is this real?

05:48.917 --> 05:51.125
-Mommy, what's happening?
-I'm not sure, sweetie.

05:51.208 --> 05:52.959
[Nana Ante] Winston,
I've been waiting for this day

05:53.041 --> 05:55.166
since I could cradle you in my arms.

05:55.250 --> 05:58.792
And I know you went to a lot of
trouble to get us here,

05:58.875 --> 06:00.208
-but this--
-This is broke.

06:00.291 --> 06:01.250
[Catherine] Ha!

06:01.333 --> 06:04.250
Oh, I am so sorry. Oh, I'm so sorry.

06:04.333 --> 06:07.041
No disrespect, Meredith.
You have a lovely home.

06:07.125 --> 06:11.291
-But, Maggie, your own sister isn't here!
-Amelia had to be on call today.

06:11.375 --> 06:14.709
Right, should she let someone
die of a stroke just to be here with us?

06:14.792 --> 06:17.667
But even if she was here,
you have more family.

06:17.750 --> 06:19.583
You have uncles, aunts, cousins.

06:19.667 --> 06:22.291
I have a savings account for your wedding,

06:22.375 --> 06:23.291
to do this right.

06:23.375 --> 06:26.875
[Nana Ante] In a church.
Or at least with more than 10 people.

06:26.959 --> 06:29.458
Do you know how proud we are of you two?

06:29.542 --> 06:30.959
We want the world to see.

06:31.041 --> 06:34.959
But it isn't safe right now, Nana Ante.
We can't do it that way.

06:35.041 --> 06:37.208
Well, then wait. What's the hurry?

06:37.291 --> 06:39.375
You all are already living together.

06:39.458 --> 06:41.041
[clears throat]

06:42.333 --> 06:45.583
So, uh...we wait?

06:49.333 --> 06:51.750
[sighs] Yeah, I guess so.

06:52.834 --> 06:54.250
I'll get the champagne.

06:54.333 --> 06:55.583
-Yeah.
-Vodka, please.

06:55.667 --> 06:58.750
-Can I cut the cake?
-Just wait a minute, okay, honey?

06:58.834 --> 07:00.500
You can do whatever you want, sweetie.

07:00.583 --> 07:02.542
Okay, she said you can go get cake!

07:02.625 --> 07:03.667
You wanna take this?

07:03.750 --> 07:05.250
Great, thank you.

07:05.333 --> 07:07.375
-[Link] Champagne, anyone?
-I'll take that.

07:08.834 --> 07:10.291
-Thanks.
-Mm-hmm.

07:11.375 --> 07:13.041
[Maggie] Bottoms up, everyone!

07:14.333 --> 07:17.291
Captioning provided by
ABC Studios and ABC, Inc.

07:25.417 --> 07:28.667
[woman over P.A.]
<i>Dr. Sellers, </i><i>Dr. Mari Sellers, 4619.</i>

07:28.750 --> 07:32.375
Uh, technically, I still haven't
signed the discharge paperwork.

07:32.458 --> 07:36.208
I-- I know, but I've never
missed a month of work in my life,

07:36.291 --> 07:37.792
and they need me.

07:37.875 --> 07:41.083
I heard Earl took his pants off
during Arts &amp; Crafts.

07:41.166 --> 07:42.417
-Twice.
-[laughs]

07:42.500 --> 07:44.125
You were on a vent for two weeks.

07:44.208 --> 07:47.208
I know at your facility
it's all hands on deck, but--

07:47.291 --> 07:50.083
Take it easy and go slow.

07:50.166 --> 07:52.750
Yes, Dr. Bailey,
I know the recommendations.

07:52.834 --> 07:54.792
Oh, so you know they apply to you also?

07:54.875 --> 07:56.125
Mm-hmm.

07:56.667 --> 07:58.458
Come on, let's have one last listen.

07:59.583 --> 08:01.500
May I take a listen first, Chief?

08:01.583 --> 08:02.750
I don't have a lot of experience

08:02.834 --> 08:04.583
listening to lungs
that have recovered from COVID,

08:04.667 --> 08:07.500
and I think it'll be really
beneficial to my education.

08:09.959 --> 08:12.041
-Fine.
-Yes!

08:14.291 --> 08:17.166
Just take a few deep breaths
for me, please.

08:20.458 --> 08:21.625
Love.

08:21.709 --> 08:22.875
Does that mean I can go?

08:22.959 --> 08:25.542
Uh, no, I'll still need to take
a listen of my own.

08:25.625 --> 08:26.709
[giggles]

08:26.792 --> 08:27.709
"Love."

08:28.125 --> 08:29.375
[ship horn blows]

08:29.458 --> 08:32.709
The rush I felt when I watched that woman,

08:32.792 --> 08:35.542
who'd been in a coma for weeks,

08:35.625 --> 08:38.291
whom I could only talk to via MRI,

08:38.375 --> 08:40.291
leave the hospital with her father--

08:40.375 --> 08:44.125
the relief and the joy and the hope--

08:44.208 --> 08:45.709
I mean, I felt that for, like...

08:47.542 --> 08:49.250
30 seconds.

08:49.333 --> 08:50.667
And then just...

08:50.750 --> 08:54.041
all the worst-case scenarios
started screaming in my head.

08:54.125 --> 08:56.000
I mean, not for her, for-- for me.

08:56.083 --> 08:58.583
For my family. My son.

08:59.417 --> 09:03.000
And I don't know why my thinking
is so dark, except...

09:04.417 --> 09:05.709
addict.

09:07.417 --> 09:09.375
But it's been a year. Um...

09:10.583 --> 09:12.834
So much. So much fear.

09:12.917 --> 09:14.667
[inhales deeply] So much fear.

09:14.750 --> 09:16.125
[chuckles]

09:16.208 --> 09:17.959
And I know you guys all get it.

09:19.583 --> 09:23.583
And my boyfriend,
my, um, child's father...

09:24.750 --> 09:27.333
he is not one of us. [laughs]

09:27.417 --> 09:29.166
And I am so glad

09:29.250 --> 09:31.375
that he does not have to
go through life like that.

09:31.458 --> 09:32.792
Um, but...

09:33.375 --> 09:36.875
sometimes, there's a part of me
that wishes he got it.

09:36.959 --> 09:39.792
You know, just, uh... really got it.

09:41.125 --> 09:42.625
I feel lonely in it.

09:43.458 --> 09:44.458
So...

09:46.291 --> 09:47.375
I'm here.

09:47.458 --> 09:49.375
[female chairperson]
<i>Thanks, Amelia. Jason?</i>

09:49.458 --> 09:51.583
<i>Hi, I'm Jason. </i><i>I'm an addict.</i>

09:51.667 --> 09:53.417
"And all the king's men

09:53.500 --> 09:56.083
couldn't put Humpty together again."

09:56.667 --> 09:57.709
-[Luna crying]
-Hmm.

09:57.792 --> 09:59.208
Huh. Should've let the women try.

09:59.291 --> 10:00.792
What do you think, Luna?

10:01.959 --> 10:04.166
All this talk of eggs
is making her hungry.

10:04.250 --> 10:05.250
Can I get her bottle?

10:06.917 --> 10:08.917
-Humpty Dumpty's an egg?
-Isn't he?

10:09.000 --> 10:11.291
Looks like someone's got an appetite.

10:12.625 --> 10:14.667
Yep, eating like a champ.

10:14.750 --> 10:16.291
I'm glad. Everything else good?

10:16.375 --> 10:17.792
Yeah. Just checked her vitals.

10:18.750 --> 10:20.250
How long until she's discharged?

10:20.333 --> 10:24.875
She's still pending an upper GI study
and pre-albumin we need to monitor, so...

10:24.959 --> 10:27.875
But if you had to ballpark it.
Days, weeks, months?

10:27.959 --> 10:29.417
I'm sorry. It's too early to say.

10:29.792 --> 10:31.375
I know you want to get started
with a placement.

10:31.458 --> 10:34.709
I've already got a family interested
in fostering to adopt. They're perfect.

10:34.792 --> 10:37.375
They don't mind the extra attention
that she's gonna need,

10:37.458 --> 10:40.166
but they did ask for a timeline,
so keep me posted.

10:42.667 --> 10:44.875
You want me to foster Luna?

10:45.500 --> 10:48.417
Just on paper. I would do all of the work.

10:48.500 --> 10:49.959
All of the...everything.

10:50.041 --> 10:53.500
I-- I know that I'm asking a lot,
but I am out of options and time.

10:53.583 --> 10:55.750
And you-- you are--

10:55.834 --> 10:57.875
you are stable and good.

10:57.959 --> 10:59.250
You already have a kid.

10:59.333 --> 11:01.041
You're a doctor, which might be a plus

11:01.125 --> 11:02.458
for a baby with medical issues.

11:02.542 --> 11:05.041
And unlike me, your background
check will be spotless.

11:05.125 --> 11:06.458
Link, [sighs]

11:06.542 --> 11:08.792
I have never loved anybody like this,

11:08.875 --> 11:10.959
and the idea of her going to
live with somebody else,

11:11.041 --> 11:12.917
it just-- it carves out my stomach.

11:13.000 --> 11:15.917
I can't lose her. I-- I can't.

11:18.917 --> 11:21.417
-I-It's-- It's temporary?
-It's temporary!

11:21.500 --> 11:24.083
A-And-- And we will eventually
transfer custody to me.

11:24.166 --> 11:25.917
And-- And you probably won't
even have to take her home,

11:26.000 --> 11:27.750
because she can't leave the hospital yet.

11:28.333 --> 11:30.500
Please, Link, please.

11:32.291 --> 11:33.291
[sighs]

11:34.542 --> 11:35.583
Jo...

11:36.375 --> 11:37.792
I-I'm saying yes.

11:37.875 --> 11:39.291
[sighs]

11:40.000 --> 11:41.542
Amelia...

11:42.417 --> 11:44.083
[sighs] You know, w-we'll figure it out.

11:44.166 --> 11:45.458
Hell, she'd probably do the same thing.

11:45.542 --> 11:47.625
So, Jo, my answer is yes.

11:47.709 --> 11:49.542
Of course it's yes. It's you.

11:50.834 --> 11:52.333
But you're cool if I change
her name, right?

11:52.417 --> 11:53.959
-Shut up.
-Hear me out--

11:54.041 --> 11:55.875
-Hildegard.
-[both laugh]

11:55.959 --> 11:59.208
[sirens wailing in distance]

11:59.291 --> 12:01.208
-[clears throat]
-[sighs]

12:01.291 --> 12:02.375
How could this happen?

12:02.458 --> 12:03.750
COVID's just a numbers game.

12:03.834 --> 12:05.417
Oh, do you think that
it's a false positive?

12:05.500 --> 12:07.000
I don't know, that's why
I'm testing you again.

12:07.083 --> 12:08.333
What about the kids? What about you?

12:08.417 --> 12:09.750
-Your mom--
-Teddy, I'm negative.

12:09.834 --> 12:10.959
And you don't have any symptoms.

12:11.041 --> 12:13.125
Let's just follow the protocol.
We're gonna be okay.

12:13.750 --> 12:15.333
What if I'm not?

12:15.417 --> 12:17.500
-Meredith was--
-Teddy.

12:17.583 --> 12:18.542
We'll be okay.

12:18.959 --> 12:21.000
Let's not worry about anything
until we have to.

12:21.083 --> 12:23.667
Go home, get in bed.
My mom will take the kids.

12:23.750 --> 12:25.000
-I have to go.
-Mm-hmm.

12:28.500 --> 12:31.542
[Amelia] You're adopting a baby
for your friend?

12:31.625 --> 12:33.041
It's fostering.

12:33.125 --> 12:36.375
It's just to get Luna off the market
while Jo figures out the legal stuff.

12:36.458 --> 12:38.041
-And if she doesn't?
-She will.

12:38.125 --> 12:40.083
But if she doesn't?

12:40.166 --> 12:43.625
Then I guess we'll have
a daughter. [laughs]

12:43.709 --> 12:45.625
Bad joke. Okay, that won't happen.

12:45.709 --> 12:48.291
I promise, Amelia,
this is just a technicality.

12:48.375 --> 12:50.500
And really, what other choice did I have?

12:50.583 --> 12:53.917
We didn't think twice when--
when Mer needed our help.

12:54.000 --> 12:57.792
Meredith is my sister
and her kids are my family.

12:57.875 --> 13:00.583
But they're not mine. Technically.

13:00.667 --> 13:02.709
But I love them, so I did it.

13:04.792 --> 13:06.333
Is this really a problem?

13:07.500 --> 13:08.750
[stammers] Of course not.

13:08.834 --> 13:11.250
-[cellphone vibrating]
-It's just surprising.

13:11.333 --> 13:12.667
I mean, it's only
for a little while, right?

13:13.166 --> 13:14.834
-You're sure?
-Go to your surgery.

13:14.917 --> 13:16.333
I'm fine. [chuckles]

13:16.417 --> 13:17.750
Thank you.

13:17.834 --> 13:21.792
♪

13:21.875 --> 13:23.792
[door opens]

13:23.875 --> 13:25.500
[door closes]

13:25.583 --> 13:29.959
♪

13:30.041 --> 13:32.625
I've been in the hospital for a month.

13:32.709 --> 13:35.542
Forgot what the sky looked like.

13:35.625 --> 13:37.583
COVID?

13:37.667 --> 13:38.917
I had it, too.

13:39.000 --> 13:42.792
Well, if you're back at work,
that seems encouraging, right?

13:43.834 --> 13:45.333
Do you sit at a desk?

13:45.709 --> 13:47.125
-Nurse.
-Oh.

13:48.709 --> 13:51.125
Everyone recovers differently, I think.

13:51.208 --> 13:52.959
I'm still taking it easy.

13:53.041 --> 13:56.542
Continuing shortness of breath,
fatigue, lingering cough...

13:56.625 --> 13:59.625
Sounds like recovery's a blast.

13:59.709 --> 14:02.208
-[coughs]
-They don't happen all at once.

14:02.291 --> 14:04.208
What about the survivor's guilt?

14:04.709 --> 14:06.208
That doesn't go away.

14:06.291 --> 14:07.709
-My ride's here.
-Okay.

14:07.792 --> 14:09.959
Autzen? Thank you.

14:11.125 --> 14:14.625
-Take care of yourself.
-Thank you for-- for being honest.

14:14.709 --> 14:15.917
I'm-- I'm Gerlie.

14:16.000 --> 14:17.250
I'm Meredith.

14:19.834 --> 14:20.917
[wheezing]

14:21.000 --> 14:22.333
Are you okay?

14:22.417 --> 14:23.500
Dr. Grey!

14:23.583 --> 14:24.750
Gerlie!

14:24.834 --> 14:26.834
Call a rapid response. I need a gurney!

14:26.875 --> 14:28.542
Gerlie?

14:28.625 --> 14:30.166
Gerlie?

14:35.667 --> 14:40.250
♪

14:40.333 --> 14:42.250
Canceled? What?

14:45.500 --> 14:47.750
[groaning] Grey...

14:47.834 --> 14:48.792
Hey, hey.

14:48.875 --> 14:51.083
Uh, what happened to Grand Rounds?

14:51.166 --> 14:54.083
Oh, well, Gerlie's
post-COVID complications

14:54.166 --> 14:55.417
are far more instructional.

14:55.500 --> 14:57.250
She's got a pneumothorax,

14:57.333 --> 15:00.750
she's day 14 post-op from
a very complicated VATS procedure,

15:00.834 --> 15:03.083
and now she has multifocal pneumonia.

15:03.166 --> 15:05.250
Oh, so...

15:05.333 --> 15:07.291
Grand Rounds aren't canceled,
they're just postponed.

15:07.375 --> 15:10.458
It would have to be a really slow day
to make it worthwhile.

15:10.542 --> 15:13.083
[scoffs] But i-it's tradition.

15:13.166 --> 15:16.250
I-I can't tell you all that I learned
in Richard's presentations.

15:16.333 --> 15:17.917
Yeah, but the last thing
people need right now

15:18.000 --> 15:20.083
is to listen to someone talk
about how surgery works,

15:20.166 --> 15:22.500
especially after the year they've had.

15:22.583 --> 15:24.917
If you're dying to listen to
someone talk about surgery,

15:25.000 --> 15:27.583
I've invited the class
to watch me do Gerlie's bronch.

15:27.667 --> 15:28.959
You're more than welcome to attend.

15:29.667 --> 15:31.166
You're doing it yourself?

15:31.250 --> 15:33.917
I've been back three months
and have not operated.

15:34.000 --> 15:36.750
[stammers] Are you ready? You sure?

15:36.834 --> 15:38.667
It's just a bronch and some cultures.

15:39.333 --> 15:42.959
Don't forget, you gave me this job to
change things. So that's what I'm doing.

15:43.041 --> 15:43.917
Uh...

15:44.000 --> 15:45.500
[woman over P.A.]
<i>Dr. Blast </i><i>to nuclear medicine.</i>

15:45.583 --> 15:46.500
Okay.

15:46.583 --> 15:49.291
[Jo] Okay, great. Thank you.

15:49.375 --> 15:52.166
-Hey, listen--
-Oh, no, you first.

15:52.250 --> 15:54.166
Okay, I realized something

15:54.250 --> 15:56.709
that's going to make your
foster application a shoo-in,

15:56.792 --> 15:58.625
owning part of the hospital!

15:58.709 --> 16:01.125
How nice of you to think of me.

16:01.208 --> 16:04.792
Ugh! I need the money
for stupid adoption legal fees

16:04.875 --> 16:07.458
and a family-sized home,
but nobody wants my shares

16:07.542 --> 16:10.250
because hospitals are just bleeding money
during the pandemic

16:10.333 --> 16:12.458
and it's, quote,
"the worst investment of all time."

16:12.542 --> 16:14.125
Really selling me on the idea.

16:14.208 --> 16:16.625
Okay, I didn't want to
have to go down this route,

16:16.709 --> 16:18.792
but as part owner, I'm kinda your boss.

16:18.875 --> 16:20.917
So I could just order you to buy them.

16:21.000 --> 16:23.959
Okay, but then wouldn't I be your boss
and I could just make you buy them back?

16:24.041 --> 16:25.166
-Some friend.
-[chuckles]

16:25.250 --> 16:26.291
-Sorry, Jo.
-Ah!

16:26.375 --> 16:30.250
It's a no. But I really hope
you figure out something fast because...

16:30.333 --> 16:31.500
I got approved to foster.

16:31.583 --> 16:33.458
What? Really? What?

16:33.542 --> 16:35.458
-Why didn't you tell me?
-You went first!

16:35.542 --> 16:36.625
-Oh, my God. [squeals]
-[laughs]

16:36.709 --> 16:37.709
Thank you!

16:37.792 --> 16:39.208
Okay, I have to tell Luna!

16:39.291 --> 16:40.625
[gasps]

16:43.291 --> 16:46.875
[Amelia] So, the social worker came
and looked through our place,

16:46.959 --> 16:50.959
uh, so we can get ready to foster a baby
that is never gonna be ours.

16:51.041 --> 16:54.959
And, um, the social worker
gave us this to-do list

16:55.041 --> 16:57.542
to get the place ready for a second kid,

16:57.625 --> 17:00.959
and, uh, my boyfriend
is just diving right into the project.

17:01.041 --> 17:05.208
And, um, when I reminded him
that it was temporary,

17:05.291 --> 17:06.333
he was like...

17:07.125 --> 17:10.208
"Yeah, but we'll need it one day."

17:10.291 --> 17:15.458
Meaning, one day, when we have
a second kid of our own.

17:15.542 --> 17:17.375
And it just feels...

17:18.709 --> 17:21.500
It just feels like
I don't want what he wants.

17:23.375 --> 17:25.834
And I don't know
if that's diseased thinking or...

17:27.375 --> 17:28.875
if it's just me.

17:30.375 --> 17:34.208
Marriage and more kids, um...

17:35.709 --> 17:37.083
I don't want it.

17:37.166 --> 17:39.166
And... [inhales shakily]

17:39.250 --> 17:41.208
I can't tell him.

17:41.291 --> 17:42.750
And I'm mad.

17:43.959 --> 17:45.458
Not at him. He's...

17:46.625 --> 17:48.583
nothing but wonderful, and...

17:48.667 --> 17:50.083
I'm mad at me.

17:52.625 --> 17:56.333
And I know that all of this
would be unimaginably worse

17:56.792 --> 18:00.041
and more confusing if I was high, so...

18:01.834 --> 18:03.792
since I can't be sure of anything,

18:05.667 --> 18:07.208
I'm just being sure of that.

18:07.291 --> 18:12.333
♪

18:15.625 --> 18:18.291
-Owen?
-Happy end of quarantine.

18:19.291 --> 18:21.709
-Maybe we should wait one more day.
-Teddy...

18:21.792 --> 18:23.208
I mean, just to be sure.

18:23.291 --> 18:25.291
Listen. The kids are fine.

18:26.125 --> 18:27.375
We're all testing negative,

18:27.458 --> 18:29.041
and there's no patients testing positive.

18:29.125 --> 18:31.875
-Okay. Good. That's-- That's good.
-Yeah.

18:31.959 --> 18:33.208
How you feeling?

18:33.291 --> 18:36.750
Got my energy back.
And no fever, no cough.

18:36.834 --> 18:39.917
I mean, I did sneeze maybe once.

18:40.000 --> 18:41.959
[laughs] Teddy, come out.

18:42.041 --> 18:43.625
Okay? You're safe.

18:43.709 --> 18:47.834
And Leo made me bring you
a very special celebration meal.

18:48.417 --> 18:49.792
-Mac and cheese?
-Yep.

18:49.875 --> 18:51.291
In a mug.

18:51.375 --> 18:53.750
He was very adamant about
it being in a dinosaur mug.

18:54.333 --> 18:56.208
-I miss them.
-Yeah.

18:57.166 --> 18:59.125
[sighing] Okay...

18:59.709 --> 19:01.041
Here we go.

19:04.917 --> 19:06.417
Hey.

19:08.083 --> 19:09.750
You look tired.

19:11.583 --> 19:12.917
You look beautiful.

19:14.250 --> 19:15.291
Owen, I just--

19:15.375 --> 19:20.834
♪

19:21.542 --> 19:24.709
-Wow.
-Two weeks is a really long time.

19:27.709 --> 19:30.792
Schmitt, look at all this
fibrosis and scar tissue.

19:30.875 --> 19:32.291
I can't believe it's this bad.

19:33.709 --> 19:34.875
Culture tube.

19:39.041 --> 19:40.166
Dr. Grey?

19:40.709 --> 19:42.083
Is everything okay?

19:43.291 --> 19:45.750
[inhales sharply] Saline flush.

19:45.834 --> 19:48.291
-And someone get me a wheelchair.
-Okay.

19:49.583 --> 19:50.417
What's going on?

19:50.500 --> 19:52.625
Phew. I'm dizzy.

19:52.709 --> 19:56.125
My breath is shallow.
My heart rate has gotta be in the 100s.

19:56.208 --> 19:57.875
Should we page Chief Bailey?

19:59.959 --> 20:01.250
I'm coming in.

20:01.333 --> 20:05.875
♪

20:10.959 --> 20:13.166
We maxed Gerlie out on the vent
in the middle of the night.

20:13.250 --> 20:14.667
She still wasn't saturating well.

20:14.750 --> 20:17.000
Then about an hour ago,
she coded for the second time.

20:17.083 --> 20:19.166
Why didn't you call me
when she coded the first time?

20:19.250 --> 20:20.458
It's Christmas Eve!

20:20.542 --> 20:22.041
I thought you'd be
with your kids, or, you know,

20:22.125 --> 20:24.041
-wrapping presents, baking cookies--
-Stop talking.

20:24.125 --> 20:25.458
You put her on ECMO?

20:25.542 --> 20:28.125
She's young, I saw no other
comorbidities in her chart,

20:28.208 --> 20:31.625
and I've seen patients walk out of here
weeks later after being on it.

20:31.709 --> 20:33.166
I'm sorry, I know that
Gerlie is your patient,

20:33.250 --> 20:34.250
but it was an active code.

20:34.333 --> 20:36.083
No, it's okay. It was the right call.

20:36.166 --> 20:37.917
All right. Uh, I'll see you tomorrow?

20:38.000 --> 20:40.000
Yes, of course. Merry Christmas, Altman.

20:40.083 --> 20:40.959
Merry Christmas.

20:42.166 --> 20:45.208
-[bells jingling]
-Merry Christmas!

20:45.291 --> 20:49.166
These guys will keep you company
and play you music

20:49.250 --> 20:51.667
and stimulate your extraocular muscles.

20:52.583 --> 20:54.583
-Jo.
-[gasps] Yeah?

20:56.041 --> 20:57.166
What do you think?

20:57.250 --> 20:59.500
I thought it was pretty clear
we were just doing the baby thing.

20:59.583 --> 21:02.208
That would be funny if I wasn't worried
Amelia was gonna say it.

21:02.291 --> 21:03.458
Wait, you guys haven't
talked about marriage

21:03.542 --> 21:05.834
since she said
she didn't want to get married?

21:05.917 --> 21:08.667
She also said that she didn't
<i>not </i>want to get married.

21:08.750 --> 21:10.333
She just didn't want it
to feel compulsory,

21:10.417 --> 21:11.709
and I've been planning this for weeks.

21:12.417 --> 21:14.417
[sighs] It's too small, right?

21:14.917 --> 21:17.166
[gasps] You got another diamond ring?

21:17.250 --> 21:19.166
I'm not stupid. I got a sapphire, too.

21:19.250 --> 21:20.291
Okay, stop. This is getting weird.

21:20.375 --> 21:22.583
-I need your advice!
-Okay, I--

21:22.667 --> 21:26.083
I am <i>your </i>best friend, not hers,
so I'm not sure which one she'd like.

21:26.166 --> 21:29.041
Um, you know, she's--
They're all so beautiful.

21:29.125 --> 21:30.542
She's gonna love whatever you pick.

21:30.625 --> 21:31.500
Should I have gotten a fourth?

21:31.583 --> 21:34.959
Okay, you're literally holding the value
of three of my lofts in your hand.

21:35.667 --> 21:37.250
Here goes nothing. Wish me luck.

21:37.333 --> 21:39.583
Good luck. And merry Christmas!

21:41.500 --> 21:42.417
[door closes]

21:44.834 --> 21:47.333
[door opens, closes]

21:50.792 --> 21:52.917
-Holidays are hard.
-Huh?

21:53.291 --> 21:55.208
For me, anyway.

21:55.291 --> 21:57.250
It's when I miss Abigail
the most, you know.

21:57.333 --> 21:59.083
Oh. Yeah. Joy to the world.

21:59.166 --> 22:00.792
I was just hoping that dying patients

22:00.875 --> 22:04.208
who've recovered from COVID
were eligible for lung transplants.

22:04.291 --> 22:05.750
What a world that would be.

22:05.834 --> 22:07.250
Got you a present.

22:07.333 --> 22:08.542
Might help.

22:08.625 --> 22:10.125
A present?

22:12.166 --> 22:14.250
It's open and half-empty.

22:14.333 --> 22:15.458
Short notice.

22:16.959 --> 22:21.166
Unless you'd rather pass out again
to get out of this...

22:27.583 --> 22:29.041
Sláinte.

22:29.583 --> 22:30.917
Whatever you said.

22:31.750 --> 22:33.834
<i>♪ Paper and ribbon ♪</i>

22:33.917 --> 22:35.875
<i>♪ Candles glow in window panes ♪</i>

22:35.959 --> 22:37.709
Bailey, wait your turn.

22:37.792 --> 22:41.041
[Amelia] Okay, Leo,
this one is from Auntie Amelia.

22:41.125 --> 22:42.250
And Uncle Link.

22:42.333 --> 22:45.083
Uh, no, this one is just
from Auntie Amelia.

22:45.166 --> 22:46.959
-Whoa!
-It's a brain!

22:47.083 --> 22:50.500
-Yay!
-It's educational <i>and </i>fun.

22:50.583 --> 22:54.083
Yep, that one is definitely
just from Aunt Amelia.

22:54.166 --> 22:56.667
Now, uh, I've got one for you, Amelia.

22:56.750 --> 22:58.041
Whoa, look. It's snowing.

22:58.834 --> 23:00.041
-Snowing!
-It's snowing?

23:00.125 --> 23:01.417
What? What?

23:01.500 --> 23:02.875
Why is it snowing only in the backyard?

23:02.959 --> 23:05.250
[Owen] That's weird. Let's go see
what's up. Come on. Let's go.

23:05.792 --> 23:09.875
<i>♪ Sending cards to loved ones</i>
<i>We never get to see ♪</i>

23:09.959 --> 23:11.041
Look at this!

23:11.792 --> 23:16.333
Why is it snowing outside my bedroom?

23:16.417 --> 23:18.375
What's happening?

23:18.458 --> 23:20.750
Look at this! Do you believe this?

23:20.834 --> 23:23.041
You got me snow for Christmas.

23:23.125 --> 23:24.125
[chuckles]

23:24.208 --> 23:26.208
It's snowing!

23:26.291 --> 23:28.208
-[gasps] Oh, my God.
-[gasps]

23:28.291 --> 23:29.709
-Oh, come on, man.
-Oh, my God.

23:29.792 --> 23:32.083
Theodora Grace Altman...

23:32.166 --> 23:34.208
Now, this is not the first time
I've asked you this.

23:35.291 --> 23:38.250
And we've hurt each other, I know,

23:38.333 --> 23:40.250
but we have forgiven each other.

23:40.333 --> 23:42.083
We may not make sense
to the rest of the world,

23:42.166 --> 23:44.083
but we make sense to us.

23:44.166 --> 23:46.458
So I am asking you, in front of everyone--

23:46.542 --> 23:48.041
-Including your ex-wife.
-[laughter]

23:48.709 --> 23:52.625
Would you please continue to
make me the happiest man alive?

23:52.709 --> 23:53.709
Yes. Yes.

23:53.792 --> 23:57.458
-Yay!
-Oh, my God! Wow!

23:57.542 --> 23:59.709
-Whee!
-[gasps]

23:59.792 --> 24:02.208
Yes, yes, yes.

24:03.125 --> 24:07.542
<i>♪ Paper and ribbon seem to be everywhere ♪</i>

24:14.667 --> 24:15.917
♪

24:16.000 --> 24:17.083
<i>♪ Hey! ♪</i>

24:17.166 --> 24:18.583
[vocalizing]

24:18.667 --> 24:23.834
♪

24:25.500 --> 24:26.458
<i>♪ Hey! ♪</i>

24:26.542 --> 24:28.750
[vocalizing]

24:28.834 --> 24:29.917
<i>♪ Hey! ♪</i>

24:30.000 --> 24:33.667
<i>♪ When you're looking up at the sky ♪</i>

24:33.750 --> 24:37.667
<i>♪ I will always be where you are ♪</i>

24:37.834 --> 24:42.333
<i>♪ Oh, oh, oh, our love carries on ♪</i>

24:42.417 --> 24:46.500
<i>♪ So go, go, go back where you belong ♪</i>

24:46.583 --> 24:50.458
[vocalizing]

24:50.542 --> 24:54.166
<i>♪ When you're looking up at the sky ♪</i>

24:54.250 --> 24:57.959
<i>♪ I will always be where you are ♪</i>

24:58.917 --> 25:01.125
Well, Hunt says that the whole staff

25:01.208 --> 25:03.834
should have their first dose
by the end of the day.

25:03.917 --> 25:05.500
-I love needles.
-[laughs]

25:07.583 --> 25:08.542
[chuckles]

25:08.625 --> 25:10.750
<i>♪ Back where you belong ♪</i>

25:12.417 --> 25:14.333
<i>♪ Back where you belong ♪</i>

25:14.417 --> 25:15.375
Yes, yes.

25:16.000 --> 25:17.083
[Meredith] Hi.

25:17.166 --> 25:20.750
We need to put Gerlie on the list
for a double lung transplant.

25:20.834 --> 25:22.583
[scoffs] Grey, I am in my joy.

25:22.667 --> 25:26.583
Do not take me out of my joy
to remind me of something we shouldn't do.

25:26.667 --> 25:27.834
She can handle it.

25:27.917 --> 25:30.166
Her hemoglobin has been stable
for weeks now,

25:30.250 --> 25:31.959
but her lungs are not improving.

25:32.041 --> 25:34.959
If this is the part where
you remind me of her cousins

25:35.041 --> 25:40.333
or how she rescues puppies
or buys groceries for old folks

25:40.417 --> 25:43.125
or sends half of her paycheck
to her family in Manila

25:43.208 --> 25:44.792
and deserves to live, I--

25:44.875 --> 25:46.291
I know who she is, right?

25:46.375 --> 25:49.417
The work she does, the lives she's saved.

25:49.500 --> 25:51.875
I-I know what she deserves.

25:51.959 --> 25:54.375
But Gerlie recovered from COVID.

25:54.458 --> 25:56.417
Hey, she might recover from this.

25:56.500 --> 25:58.875
So, why risk putting her through

25:58.959 --> 26:02.542
a potentially unnecessary
and dangerous surgery?

26:02.625 --> 26:04.709
So, we're just supposed to wait
and hope she lives?

26:04.792 --> 26:06.875
Or try other treatments.

26:06.959 --> 26:09.208
What if we wait too long
and she develops sepsis

26:09.291 --> 26:10.709
and is too sick for a transplant?

26:10.792 --> 26:12.375
We're not there yet.

26:13.500 --> 26:14.834
[sniffs] You took my joy.

26:14.917 --> 26:16.500
You took mine.

26:19.125 --> 26:20.709
[sighs] There you go.

26:21.792 --> 26:23.709
Oh, thank you.

26:23.792 --> 26:25.959
You are welcome.

26:26.291 --> 26:28.125
[sighs] So, uh...

26:28.792 --> 26:31.458
You didn't, uh-- didn't share today, huh?

26:31.959 --> 26:34.709
Have you gotten some clarity
with things at home?

26:34.792 --> 26:36.208
Nope.

26:36.291 --> 26:41.041
Just tired of talking myself in circles
on a subject with no answer.

26:41.125 --> 26:43.834
Well, it doesn't have to work.
You know that, right?

26:44.792 --> 26:45.875
Me and Link?

26:45.959 --> 26:47.625
You and anyone.

26:47.709 --> 26:50.291
You have a child,
you'll always have a connection.

26:50.375 --> 26:55.792
And I'm sure you love each other, so...
but it doesn't have to work.

26:57.834 --> 27:01.083
It really sounds like
you're telling me to leave him.

27:01.166 --> 27:03.583
But that also doesn't sound
like something you'd ever say.

27:03.667 --> 27:05.834
I'm definitely not telling you that.

27:07.208 --> 27:09.750
You know, something
I've noticed in recovery--

27:09.834 --> 27:11.875
you know we-- we get it in our heads

27:11.959 --> 27:16.583
that the addiction is the only reason
our lives were a mess.

27:16.667 --> 27:20.875
So we think, "Well, I'm-- I'm sober.
It should be working."

27:21.166 --> 27:23.250
And that's not always the case.

27:23.333 --> 27:26.375
And I'm not saying that either one of you
are doing anything wrong.

27:26.792 --> 27:30.750
But you're allowed to want what you want.

27:32.750 --> 27:34.959
Even if it's not what he wants.

27:36.583 --> 27:37.583
Ah.

27:37.667 --> 27:39.083
Anyway, that's my two cents.

27:39.709 --> 27:40.959
[sighs]

27:41.041 --> 27:43.083
That's like a billion cents.

27:44.375 --> 27:48.333
Eh, it's some advice I wish
I'd have been able to take in my life.

27:49.208 --> 27:50.875
Giving yourself permission

27:51.709 --> 27:53.291
for it not to work...

27:54.875 --> 27:56.917
might give you peace of mind to stay.

27:57.000 --> 28:02.166
♪

28:02.542 --> 28:04.208
[Jo] Thank you. Thank-- [sighs]

28:04.291 --> 28:07.875
Thank you so much, Anne.
This-- This means the world to me.

28:08.875 --> 28:10.875
Okay. All right, bye.

28:11.542 --> 28:14.000
-[sighs]
-Sounds like good news.

28:14.875 --> 28:19.291
Luna's lawyer is a shark.
I am definitely getting custody.

28:20.917 --> 28:23.333
Oh, congratulations, Wilson.

28:23.417 --> 28:27.250
Oh, I'm so thrilled for you and Luna.

28:27.333 --> 28:29.417
Hey, if you need a character
reference or whatever,

28:29.500 --> 28:30.667
-just let me know.
-Thank you.

28:30.750 --> 28:32.083
All right.

28:34.417 --> 28:37.417
She <i>is </i>expensive, though.

28:37.500 --> 28:39.250
Is this you asking me for a raise?

28:39.333 --> 28:44.500
No, this is me telling you
that I sold my shares of the hospital.

28:45.333 --> 28:49.166
And you're...wincing? What, bad price?

28:49.250 --> 28:51.834
Maybe I should just let the person
who bought them tell you.

28:51.917 --> 28:53.000
Hmm?

28:53.083 --> 28:54.333
[line ringing]

28:54.417 --> 28:56.166
[Koracick] <i>Miranda!</i>
<i>Did you hear the good news?</i>

28:56.250 --> 28:57.542
Wilson. You didn't.

28:57.625 --> 29:00.041
<i>You know, it's easy </i><i>to push for change</i>
<i>when you don't feel </i><i>the consequences.</i>

29:00.125 --> 29:01.333
<i>I wanted some skin </i><i>in the game.</i>

29:01.417 --> 29:03.208
I offered you a character reference!

29:03.291 --> 29:04.417
<i>You won't even know </i><i>I'm here.</i>

29:04.500 --> 29:08.291
<i>Aside from board meetings,</i>
<i>expense reports, </i><i>weekly progress reports.</i>

29:08.375 --> 29:09.667
Okay, talk to you later, Tom.

29:09.750 --> 29:10.959
<i>-Wait, I--</i>
-[cellphone beeps]

29:11.041 --> 29:12.291
[sighs]

29:12.375 --> 29:14.041
Should I...?

29:14.125 --> 29:15.417
Yeah, I should just...

29:16.125 --> 29:18.333
Thanks again. Thank you.

29:19.917 --> 29:21.834
-[scoffs]
-[cellphone vibrates]

29:21.917 --> 29:23.083
Wha--?

29:23.166 --> 29:25.917
Gerlie has shown no improvement
since going on ECMO.

29:26.000 --> 29:29.375
Oh, she's alive. That's an improvement.
So, treatment options.

29:29.458 --> 29:30.667
Double lung transplant.

29:30.750 --> 29:33.250
Yes, but since she could suffer
additional bleeding

29:33.333 --> 29:35.625
or sudden death, that is not an option.

29:35.709 --> 29:37.041
But it could be. If you made it one.

29:37.125 --> 29:38.542
Thank you, Helm. Who else?

29:38.625 --> 29:40.208
Uh... Ortiz.

29:40.291 --> 29:42.834
So, at first, I considered
monoclonal antibodies.

29:42.917 --> 29:44.375
-Mm-hmm.
-But then it hit me--

29:44.458 --> 29:46.667
double lung transplant
makes the most sense.

29:46.750 --> 29:50.125
Anyone have any suggestions
other than double lung transplant?

29:50.834 --> 29:51.875
Thank you. Perez?

29:51.959 --> 29:53.583
Uh, we transplant her right lung,

29:53.667 --> 29:56.125
and...also her left.

29:57.750 --> 29:59.667
We could also try
a double lung transplant.

29:59.750 --> 30:00.709
I'm sorry.

30:00.792 --> 30:02.917
Dr. Grey said we literally
couldn't stop pitching it.

30:03.000 --> 30:04.166
[Bailey] Thank you, Schmitt.

30:04.250 --> 30:07.083
This was in no way obvious. Move.

30:09.291 --> 30:10.875
Just tell me before you do it.

30:10.959 --> 30:12.125
I'm already done.

30:12.792 --> 30:16.166
So, just ice it and drink
plenty of fluids, okay?

30:16.250 --> 30:18.166
Oh, thank you, my boy.

30:18.250 --> 30:20.000
You're sure I didn't steal it
from someone?

30:20.083 --> 30:21.417
[laughs] It was extra.

30:21.500 --> 30:24.417
I actually called our entire waiting list
before I called you.

30:24.500 --> 30:27.250
If you hadn't gotten here when you did,
I would have had to throw it in the trash,

30:27.333 --> 30:28.208
which feels like a sin.

30:28.291 --> 30:31.041
The more people that get this,
the safer we'll all be.

30:31.125 --> 30:33.834
And how long 'til I can hug you
without a mask?

30:33.917 --> 30:36.667
[chuckles] Two weeks
after your second shot, so soon.

30:36.792 --> 30:37.875
Did I miss it?

30:37.959 --> 30:39.458
Oh, I missed it.

30:39.542 --> 30:41.375
You can give me my second shot, dear.

30:41.458 --> 30:43.166
[chuckles]

30:43.250 --> 30:44.250
[sighs]

30:44.917 --> 30:47.500
[car horns honking]

30:47.583 --> 30:51.333
Okay, not only did you take my joy,

30:51.417 --> 30:56.000
I now have an army of interns
trying to do your dirty work.

30:56.917 --> 30:59.250
Double lung transplant is her best option.

30:59.333 --> 31:02.542
You are supposed to be
teaching them, Grey.

31:02.625 --> 31:03.750
This is me teaching them.

31:03.834 --> 31:06.041
We have to stop thinking about COVID

31:06.125 --> 31:08.458
in terms of who survives and who doesn't.

31:08.542 --> 31:11.667
There are millions of people
who are going to be suffering

31:11.750 --> 31:13.834
from the aftereffects of COVID,

31:13.917 --> 31:18.291
and we need to advocate for them
as hard as we advocate for everybody else.

31:18.375 --> 31:22.083
It is risky, but it is also her best shot.

31:22.166 --> 31:24.750
So, you teaching them is just...

31:24.834 --> 31:26.750
you breeding an army of little yous?

31:26.834 --> 31:28.291
No respect for legacy?

31:28.375 --> 31:31.542
Richard Webber made you. He made me.

31:31.625 --> 31:33.291
And he's going to die someday.

31:33.375 --> 31:37.125
And one day, you're going to die,
and one day, I'm going to die.

31:37.208 --> 31:39.417
And if this year has taught us anything,

31:39.500 --> 31:42.458
it's that that may happen
a lot sooner than any of us want.

31:42.542 --> 31:43.917
So I'm not going to waste any time

31:44.000 --> 31:47.083
teaching anything
other than what matters most.

31:47.166 --> 31:50.250
And Bailey, you know
if this was me or your mother,

31:50.333 --> 31:52.750
you would be screaming from the rooftops.

31:52.834 --> 31:54.917
-[scoffs]
-You know that, right?

31:55.000 --> 31:55.917
[laughs]

31:56.000 --> 31:57.750
Just please call UNOS.

31:57.834 --> 31:59.417
[sighing] Okay.

31:59.500 --> 32:01.917
You can make changes

32:02.000 --> 32:04.583
and still honor

32:04.667 --> 32:06.750
what made you.

32:06.834 --> 32:08.083
I don't know what that means.

32:08.166 --> 32:09.375
It means I'm gonna make the damn call,

32:09.458 --> 32:11.792
but you're starting back Grand Rounds.

32:11.875 --> 32:13.333
Or you're fired.

32:19.333 --> 32:25.208
♪

32:26.208 --> 32:28.208
[seagulls crying]

32:29.917 --> 32:32.000
[Zola] Mom!

32:32.083 --> 32:37.333
♪

32:39.667 --> 32:45.583
♪

32:47.166 --> 32:53.083
♪

32:54.750 --> 32:56.500
<i>♪ Talk ♪</i>

32:56.583 --> 33:00.333
<i>♪ Let's have conversations in the dark ♪</i>

33:00.417 --> 33:04.709
<i>♪ World is sleeping, I'm awake with you ♪</i>

33:05.750 --> 33:09.083
<i>♪ With you ♪</i>

33:09.583 --> 33:11.500
<i>♪ Watch ♪</i>

33:11.583 --> 33:15.000
<i>♪ Movies that we both already seen ♪</i>

33:15.458 --> 33:20.375
<i>♪ I ain't even looking at the screen</i>
<i>It's true ♪</i>

33:20.458 --> 33:24.041
<i>♪ I got my eyes on you ♪</i>

33:24.125 --> 33:27.458
<i>♪ And you say that you're not worthy ♪</i>

33:28.125 --> 33:31.709
<i>♪ You get hung up on your flaws ♪</i>

33:31.792 --> 33:34.917
<i>♪ Well, in my eyes, you are perfect ♪</i>

33:35.625 --> 33:38.208
<i>♪ As you are ♪</i>

33:40.291 --> 33:43.667
<i>♪ I will never try to change you</i>
<i>Change you ♪</i>

33:44.291 --> 33:47.875
<i>♪ I will always want the same you</i>
<i>Same you ♪</i>

33:47.959 --> 33:50.333
<i>♪ Swear on everything I pray to ♪</i>

33:51.125 --> 33:55.583
<i>♪ That I won't break your heart ♪</i>

33:55.667 --> 33:59.417
<i>♪ I'll be there when you get lonely</i>
<i>Lonely ♪</i>

33:59.500 --> 34:01.083
<i>♪ Keep the secrets that you told me</i>
<i>Told me ♪</i>

34:01.166 --> 34:03.125
[Richard] Can everyone
take their seats, please?

34:03.208 --> 34:04.125
Thank you.

34:04.208 --> 34:06.125
<i>♪ Your love is all you owe me ♪</i>

34:06.208 --> 34:07.792
<i>♪ And I won't break your heart ♪</i>

34:07.875 --> 34:12.083
It is my absolute pleasure
to be gathered with you today.

34:13.792 --> 34:17.125
<i>♪ On Sunday mornings</i>
<i>We sleep in 'til noon ♪</i>

34:17.208 --> 34:19.417
To love and to cherish.

34:19.500 --> 34:24.000
<i>♪ Well, I can sleep forever next to you ♪</i>

34:24.667 --> 34:25.917
<i>♪ Next to you ♪</i>

34:26.000 --> 34:27.625
In sickness and in health.

34:28.583 --> 34:31.500
<i>♪ And we, we got places we both gotta be ♪</i>

34:31.583 --> 34:36.000
[Richard] In Scripture, a young person
about to embark on married life says

34:36.083 --> 34:39.834
"I have found the one whom my soul loves."

34:41.166 --> 34:44.750
Maggie, Winston,
this is our prayer for you,

34:44.834 --> 34:49.125
that you may love one another
with your entire souls.

34:51.000 --> 34:54.875
<i>♪ But in my eyes, you are perfect ♪</i>

34:54.959 --> 34:56.709
<i>♪ As you are ♪</i>

34:56.792 --> 34:57.875
<i>♪ As you are ♪</i>

34:57.959 --> 35:01.750
I now pronounce you husband and wife.

35:03.041 --> 35:04.875
-Go on, kiss her.
-[laughter]

35:04.959 --> 35:07.000
<i>♪ I will always want the same you</i>
<i>Same you ♪</i>

35:07.083 --> 35:10.458
-[cheers and applause]
<i>-♪ Swear on everything I pray to ♪</i>

35:10.542 --> 35:15.125
<i>♪ That I won't break your heart ♪</i>

35:15.208 --> 35:17.959
<i>♪ I'll be there when you get lonely</i>
<i>Lonely ♪</i>

35:18.917 --> 35:21.667
<i>♪ Keep the secrets that you told me</i>
<i>Told me ♪</i>

35:21.750 --> 35:23.166
[Winston] Let's jump that broom.

35:23.250 --> 35:25.333
<i>♪ And your love is all you owe me ♪</i>

35:25.417 --> 35:26.917
1, 2, 3!

35:27.000 --> 35:29.583
<i>♪ I won't break your heart ♪</i>

35:29.667 --> 35:32.291
[cheers and applause]

35:34.417 --> 35:36.667
[Richard] All right, now, everyone, um,

35:36.750 --> 35:39.083
these two have to stick around
to take some pictures.

35:39.166 --> 35:43.417
Would the rest of you be so kind
as to head to the reception area?

35:43.500 --> 35:46.041
<i>♪ I won't break your heart ♪</i>

35:47.583 --> 35:48.834
Excuse me.

35:48.917 --> 35:52.041
Hey, so they found a donor for Gerlie.
We have to go.

35:52.125 --> 35:54.792
What-- Oh, my God.
I'm sorry we have to leave you like this.

35:54.875 --> 35:56.458
-Yeah.
-Okay.

35:56.542 --> 35:59.500
So, can you please tell Maggie
what happened?

35:59.583 --> 36:01.041
-Mm-hmm.
-And can you watch the kids?

36:01.125 --> 36:02.375
-Of course. Yeah. Go, go, go.
-Okay. All right.

36:02.458 --> 36:03.917
-Thanks.
-Okay.

36:04.917 --> 36:05.917
[sighs]

36:06.000 --> 36:08.041
You better give me a good price.

36:08.125 --> 36:10.875
The economy is trash.
You're lucky I'm even looking.

36:10.959 --> 36:12.792
[Avery] <i>Yeah, well, now that</i>
<i>you </i><i>actually have some money,</i>

36:12.875 --> 36:15.625
<i>maybe you'll, uh, </i><i>figure out how it works.</i>

36:15.709 --> 36:18.208
[laughs] I really hope you get a new joke.

36:18.291 --> 36:19.750
<i>All right. </i><i>I gotta get back to work.</i>

36:19.834 --> 36:21.375
<i>Welcome home, Jo.</i>

36:22.458 --> 36:24.625
-[beeps]
-[sighs]

36:24.709 --> 36:26.041
Welcome home.

36:27.625 --> 36:29.375
Welcome home, Luna.

36:29.458 --> 36:31.375
[Luna cooing]

36:31.458 --> 36:36.709
♪

36:37.458 --> 36:39.709
-I had a village.
-[Teddy] What?

36:39.792 --> 36:43.917
I have a village of people in my life
who wanted me to recover,

36:44.000 --> 36:46.000
pulling for me at every complication.

36:46.083 --> 36:47.375
I could literally hear them.

36:47.917 --> 36:49.333
And it helped.

36:49.417 --> 36:52.917
And Gerlie's people can't be here,
so we're her village.

36:53.417 --> 36:55.083
We're her village.

36:56.250 --> 36:58.500
[Meredith] Stay with us, Gerlie.
We got you.

36:59.917 --> 37:01.500
Scalpel, Bokhee.

37:01.583 --> 37:05.750
<i>♪ I don't fear ♪</i>

37:07.583 --> 37:11.250
<i>♪ 'Cause it won't be long now ♪</i>

37:11.333 --> 37:14.208
<i>♪ 'Cause it won't be long ♪</i>

37:14.291 --> 37:19.250
<i>♪ 'Til we're out of here ♪</i>

37:19.333 --> 37:23.750
♪

37:23.834 --> 37:26.458
-Ready for the specimen?
-I'm ready.

37:30.000 --> 37:35.250
<i>♪ I'm gonna take you home ♪</i>

37:35.333 --> 37:37.208
Ready for the donor lungs.

37:37.291 --> 37:42.625
<i>♪ I'm gonna take you home ♪</i>

37:43.834 --> 37:49.709
<i>♪ I'm gonna take you home ♪</i>

37:50.375 --> 37:56.291
♪

38:00.125 --> 38:01.542
You okay? You need a break?

38:01.625 --> 38:03.208
No, why? Do you?

38:03.250 --> 38:04.750
No.

38:04.834 --> 38:06.375
Bokhee, irrigation, please.

38:06.458 --> 38:11.375
<i>♪ Home ♪</i>

38:11.458 --> 38:17.375
<i>♪ I'm gonna take you home ♪</i>

38:19.250 --> 38:20.834
[snip echoes]

38:20.917 --> 38:26.291
♪

38:26.375 --> 38:31.750
♪

38:31.834 --> 38:37.500
<i>♪ I'm gonna take you home ♪</i>

38:38.667 --> 38:44.250
<i>♪ I'm gonna take you home ♪</i>

38:44.333 --> 38:50.250
♪

38:53.041 --> 38:58.875
♪

39:01.709 --> 39:07.542
♪

39:10.375 --> 39:12.083
Whoo!

39:12.166 --> 39:14.000
♪

39:14.083 --> 39:16.000
You've got this.

39:16.083 --> 39:21.333
♪

39:21.417 --> 39:22.834
What's going on?

39:24.542 --> 39:28.875
Well, you said you didn't want compulsory,
so here we go.

39:34.333 --> 39:37.417
I wasn't sure what style you'd like,
so I-I thought you could pick.

39:37.500 --> 39:38.917
Or you can just have all four.

39:39.000 --> 39:39.834
-Link...
-Amelia,

39:39.917 --> 39:42.875
I-I know that this last year
has been intense.

39:42.959 --> 39:45.750
Everything about us has been intense.
It's-- It's kind of our thing.

39:45.834 --> 39:47.417
I don't think it makes sense
for us to wait

39:47.500 --> 39:49.667
until life settles down,
because knowing us, it won't.

39:49.750 --> 39:53.375
But I do know that no matter what happens,
I want to go through it with you.

39:54.917 --> 39:59.917
You...challenge me, you-- you thrill me,

40:00.000 --> 40:03.333
you impress the hell out of me.

40:03.417 --> 40:05.792
There's definitely no one
on Earth like you,

40:05.875 --> 40:06.750
so please,

40:07.542 --> 40:10.834
will you do me the honor of marrying me?

40:20.917 --> 40:25.625
♪

40:26.917 --> 40:31.500
♪

40:32.917 --> 40:35.959
<i>♪ When the world was ending ♪</i>

40:36.917 --> 40:39.000
[Meredith] <i>I'm still alive.</i>

40:39.083 --> 40:42.166
<i>♪ And we talked about the places</i>
<i>We'd never been ♪</i>

40:42.250 --> 40:46.041
<i>People often laugh at that answer,</i>
<i>but it's not a joke.</i>

40:46.125 --> 40:52.041
<i>♪ When the world was ending</i>
<i>We'd hold on to the past ♪</i>

40:52.125 --> 40:53.875
Are you responsible for this?

40:53.959 --> 40:56.125
<i>♪'Cause it's all we thought</i>
<i>That </i><i>we would ever see ♪</i>

40:56.208 --> 40:59.542
You do things your way,
I'm-a do things mine.

40:59.625 --> 41:02.250
[Meredith] <i>Being alive... </i><i>it's everything.</i>

41:02.333 --> 41:05.250
<i>♪ Another day to begin again ♪</i>

41:05.333 --> 41:08.750
<i>♪ To begin again, to begin ♪</i>

41:08.834 --> 41:10.792
Okay, everybody, louder!

41:10.875 --> 41:16.834
♪ And cry because I'm happy ♪

41:17.291 --> 41:21.208
<i>♪ And hold my friends</i>
<i>Like long-lost lovers ♪</i>

41:21.291 --> 41:24.041
[Meredith] <i>Time to celebrate.</i>

41:24.125 --> 41:28.375
<i>♪ Be kind to me and love each other ♪</i>

41:28.458 --> 41:30.208
[knock on door]

41:30.291 --> 41:36.166
<i>♪ The world keeps spinning on ♪</i>

41:37.667 --> 41:40.041
<i>And yes, time for pain.</i>

41:42.000 --> 41:45.250
-Oh, Link.
<i>-♪ When the world was ending ♪</i>

41:45.333 --> 41:47.041
I'm so sorry.

41:49.250 --> 41:50.834
Do you have someplace I can crash?

41:51.667 --> 41:52.792
Yeah.

41:53.834 --> 41:56.959
<i>♪ So far from comprehending ♪</i>

41:57.041 --> 42:00.291
<i>♪ They'd lift us to the stars ♪</i>

42:00.375 --> 42:02.291
[Meredith] <i>Time to change.</i>

42:02.375 --> 42:04.125
<i>♪ Never seen each other from so far away ♪</i>

42:04.208 --> 42:05.625
<i>To grow.</i>

42:05.709 --> 42:06.792
<i>To love.</i>

42:06.875 --> 42:09.125
<i>♪ It's all right, it's okay ♪</i>

42:09.208 --> 42:12.000
♪ We will get another day ♪

42:12.083 --> 42:15.667
<i>♪ To begin again, to begin again ♪</i>

42:15.750 --> 42:19.000
<i>♪ To begin again ♪</i>

42:22.750 --> 42:24.083
Meredith.

42:24.917 --> 42:27.834
Gerlie! How are you feeling?

42:27.917 --> 42:29.750
You're still here?

42:30.917 --> 42:32.291
I'm still here.

42:32.667 --> 42:36.417
<i>♪ To begin again, to begin again</i>
<i>To begin ♪</i>

42:36.500 --> 42:37.583
<i>♪ To live ♪</i>

42:38.166 --> 42:39.709
<i>And time to give.</i>

42:40.667 --> 42:42.500
<i>♪ And breathe again ♪</i>

42:43.000 --> 42:46.417
♪

42:53.667 --> 42:55.500
[theme music playing]

42:57.583 --> 43:03.542
♪

43:04.166 --> 43:10.125
♪

43:10.625 --> 43:16.542
♪

43:17.125 --> 43:22.792
♪
